==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shog
<hw>Shog</hw> <pr>(sh⟦ocr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Shock</er> a striking.]</ety> <def>A shock; a jog; a violent
concussion or impulse.</def> <mark>[R. or Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shog</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shog
<hw>Shog</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To shake; to shock.</def> <mark>[R.
or Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shog</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shog
<hw>Shog</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. W. <ets>ysgogi</ets> to wag,
to stir. Cf. <er>Jog</er>.]</ety> <def>To jog; to move on.</def>
<mark>[R. or Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

